21. It's true there are new regulations for mercury emissions from power plants, but these will need billions of dollars to implement and increase the cost for everyone.
    确实，有新的法规限制燃煤电厂的汞排放，但这些法规需要数十亿美元来实施，并增加每个人的成本。
    - regulations 法规
    - mercury emissions 汞排放 mercury 汞/ 水星
    - power plants 燃煤电厂 plants 植物/设施，工厂 发电厂等
    - implement 实施 / carry out 执行

22. The teacher's task is to assist the student to apply what they have learned paraconsciously, and in doing so to make it easily accessible to consciousness.
    教师的工作是帮助学生有意识地应用他们所学的东西，并使它很容易被意识所接受。
    - consciously 有意识地
    - paraconsciously 潜意识地 para- 前缀，表示“超级的” paramount 至高无上的/ 派拉蒙
    - make it easily accessible to consciousness 使它很容易被意识所接受
    - in doing so 这样做 / by doing that 通过这样做

23. However, if one of the parties in a conflict sees human resource as simply mouthpiece of the chief executive, then an extenal midiator might be able to help.
    然而，如果冲突中的一方将人力资源视为首席执行官的传声筒，那么外部调解员可能会有所帮助。
    - party 一方
    - sees human resource as simply mouthpiece of the chief executive 将人力资源视为首席执行官的传声筒
    - mouthpiece 传声筒
    - external mediator 外部调解员

24. Summer leaves are green because they are full of chlorophyll, the molecule that captures sunlight and converts that energy into new building materials for the tree.
    夏天叶子是绿色的，因为它们充满了叶绿素，这种分子捕获阳光并将能量转化为树木的新建筑材料。
    - chlorophyll 叶绿素
    - molecule 分子
    - captures sunlight 捕获阳光
    - converts that energy into new building materials 将能量转化为新的建筑材料

25. If clothing fails to meet the standards, as determined by the employee's supervisor, the employee will be asked not to wear the inappropriate item to work again.
    如果服装不符合员工主管确定的标准，员工将被要求不再穿不合适的衣服去工作。
    - clothing 服装
    - fails to meet the standards 不符合标准
    - determined by the employee's supervisor 由员工主管确定
    - inappropriate item 不合适的物品
    - wear the inappropriate item to work again 穿不合适的衣服去工作
